@bberg I fully understand and I'm absolutely on your page.

I simply wasn't aware that it is supposed to **not** work. That said, some sort of:
"Your running this outside of a GNOME environment. This is not supported an things may go haywire - use at your own risk!" - message would have been perfect.

The issue comes from a [bugfix in ibus](https://github.com/ibus/ibus/commit/cca4fd8993613a6993965c3120323e43c4647ef5):

```
/* don't set focus on password entry */
    if (ibusimcontext->client_window != NULL) {
        GtkWidget *widget;

        gdk_window_get_user_data (ibusimcontext->client_window,
                                  (gpointer *)&widget);

        if (GTK_IS_ENTRY (widget) &&
            !gtk_entry_get_visibility (GTK_ENTRY (widget))) {
            return;
        }
    }
```

The commit makes sense for IBus, but form an accessibility/tablet perspective means that one cannot type passwords under Xorg.

